== Events == * In the 7th year of the Kaei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1854]] – December 23): An 8.4-magnitude earthquake—the Kaei Great Earthquake (also known as the Ansei Tōkai Earthquake)—occurred with its epicenter in Suruga Bay. More than 10,000 people died, and the Tōkaidō region was cut off. A Russian warship, the Diana, anchored at Shimoda, was severely damaged by a tsunami. * In the 3rd year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1870]] – December 25): The Tokyo Naval Depot was renamed the Naval Academy, and the Osaka Depot was renamed the Army Academy.
== Births == * In the 1st year of the Bunroku era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1592]] – December 7): Hidegen Takayuki, a Zen monk of the Ming dynasty and the founder of the Japanese Ōbaku school, was born (died 1673). * In the 8th year of the Bunsei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1825]] – December 13): Arima Shinshichi, a proponent of the Sonnō jōi movement, was born (died 1862).
== Deaths == * In the 5th year of the Ōei era ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1398]] – December 12): Ashikaga Ujimasa, a military commander, died. * In the 19th year of the Tenshō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1591]] – December 19): Hojo Ujinao, lord of Odawara Castle, died (born 1562). * In the 1st year of the Keichō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1596]] – December 23): Hattori Masanari (also known as Hattori Hanzō (Masanari)), a military commander and ninja master from Iga, died (born 1542). * In the 6th year of the Hōreki era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1756]] – November 25): The second-generation head of Takeda Izumo, known as Zabon Takeda Izumo (Oyakata Izumo), a Joruri playwright and head of the Osaka Takeda Izumo theater, died (born 1691).
