{{Lunisolar November}} 
'''November 4''' is the 4th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)}}  the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}}  day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引}} . 


== Events ==
* In the 7th year of the Kaei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1854]] – December 23): An 8.4-magnitude earthquake—the Kaei Great Earthquake (also known as the Ansei Tōkai Earthquake)—occurred with its epicenter in Suruga Bay. More than 10,000 people died, and the Tōkaidō region was cut off. A Russian warship, the Diana, anchored at Shimoda, was severely damaged by a tsunami.
* In the 3rd year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1870]] – December 25): The Tokyo Naval Depot was renamed the Naval Academy, and the Osaka Depot was renamed the Army Academy.

== Births ==
* In the 1st year of the Bunroku era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1592]] – December 7): Hidegen Takayuki, a Zen monk of the Ming dynasty and the founder of the Japanese Ōbaku school, was born (died 1673).
* In the 8th year of the Bunsei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1825]] – December 13): Arima Shinshichi, a proponent of the Sonnō jōi movement, was born (died 1862).

== Deaths ==
* In the 5th year of the Ōei era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1398]] – December 12): Ashikaga Ujimasa, a military commander, died.
* In the 19th year of the Tenshō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1591]] – December 19): Hojo Ujinao, lord of Odawara Castle, died (born 1562).
* In the 1st year of the Keichō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1596]] – December 23): Hattori Masanari (also known as Hattori Hanzō (Masanari)), a military commander and ninja master from Iga, died (born 1542).
